T1  - Reputation and performance fee effects on portfolio choice by investment advisers1I am grateful for advice from Anat Admati, Jim Anton, Faruk Gul, Robert Heinkel, David Hirshleifer, Rick Lambert, Russell Lundholm, Paul Pfleiderer, Nikos Vettas, and Jeffrey Zwiebel. I particularly thank Jack Hughes for advice and encouragement. I am grateful to an anonymous referee who suggested many useful extensions and interpretations of the original analysis. The comments of seminar participants at Stanford University, the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, Yale University, and the 1995 Western Finance Association Meetings are appreciated.1
